<h2>Add questions and answers by uploading a CSV file.<br></h2>

<p><strong>How do I create a CSV file?</strong><br>There are several ways, but the easiest is to save an Excel file as a CSV filetype (use the drop down box when you 'Save As'. Another way is to type the questions and answers in a text file, with each question on a new row, and commas separating the answers.</p><br>

<p><strong>The format of your CSV file</strong><br>The format of the file should one row per question, with the answers separated by commas. i.e.:<br>
	<br> 
	<em>question,answer,answer,answer</em> (for as many answers as you want)<br>
	<em>question,answer,answer,answer...</em><br>
	.<br>
	...for as many questions as you want.</p>

<br>
<h3>Quiz Title: <%= @quiz.title %></h3>
	<%= form_tag csv_upload_quiz_path, :multipart => true do %>  
	<%= file_field_tag :file %>
	<%= submit_tag %>
	<% end %>
